1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses information theoretic tools to analyze fundamental bounds on the optimal performance of the proposed multi-user beam alignment scheme. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication systems and proposes a practical beam alignment scheme for multi-user scenarios. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of narrow beams in millimeter wave frequency bands for wireless communication. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a beam design optimization problem for the multi-user beam alignment scheme, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the design and deployment of wireless communication systems, which can have societal impacts.
